<section begin=intro /><dfn>Spell damage</dfn> ( <math>Sp</math> ) is usually damage dealt in a separate instance from [[attack damage]], with some exceptions. This includes all abilities (including item abilities and [[attack modifier]]s) which deal the 3 [[damage types]] — [[magical]], [[physical]] or [[pure]] damage.<section end=intro />

Magic spell damage is influenced by [[magic resistance]], physical spell damage is influenced by [[armor]] and pure damage is not affected by either. All three underlie [[damage manipulation]].

==Spell Damage Manipulation==
{{Main|Damage manipulation}}
===Stacking===
All sources of spell damage manipulation stack additively within two categories, outgoing and incoming, which are then multiplied together. The two categories [[Spell damage#Outgoing Spell Damage Manipulation|Outgoing Spell Damage Manipulation]] and [[Spell damage#Incoming Spell Damage Manipulation|Incoming Spell Damage Manipulation]] stack additively with [[Damage manipulation#Incoming Damage|Generic Incoming Damage Manipulation]] and [[Damage manipulation#Outgoing Damage|Generic Outgoing Damage Manipulation]] respectively as spell damage manipulation is considered to be just a part of [[Damage manipulation]].  Since these are handled separately, the same category stack additively while different categories stack multiplicatively with each other.

For example, spell damage dealt by [[summon|summons]], unless otherwise stated, are not affected by the outgoing spell damage manipulation of the hero. However, summons can be affected by incoming spell damage manipulation since incoming spell damage manipulation affects the target of the damage instead of the caster.

Spell Damage Multiplier is defined as:

: {{#tag:math|
\text{Spell Damage Multiplier} = \big( 1 + \sum (\text{Outgoing Manip}) \big) \times \big( 1 + \sum (\text{Incoming Manip}) \big)
}}

====Example 1: Outgoing Manipulation====<!--
-->{{#vardefine:bloodrage|{{#expr:{{#explode:{{#explode:{{Show|A|Bloodseeker|Bloodrage|value3}}|/|3}}|%}}/100}}}}<!--
-->{{#vardefine:kns|{{#expr:{{Show|I|Kaya and Sange|bonus spell damage}}/100}}}}

: {{H|Bloodseeker}} with a level 4 {{A|Bloodseeker|Bloodrage}} buff with {{I|Kaya and Sange}}. What is his current spell damage multiplier?
:: Spell damage amplification values: 
::* Level 4 {{A|Bloodseeker|Bloodrage}}: {{#var:bloodrage}}
::* {{I|Kaya and Sange}}: {{#var:kns}}

: {{#tag:math|
Sp_{Mu} = (1 + {{#var:bloodrage}} + {{#var:kns}}) \times (1 + 0) = {{#vardefineecho:spellexample1|{{#expr:1+{{#var:bloodrage}}+{{#var:kns}}}}}}
}}

: {{H|Bloodseeker}}'s spell damage multiplier is {{#var:spellexample1}} in this example.

====Example 2: Incoming and Outgoing Manipulation====<!--
-->{{#vardefine:veil|{{#expr:{{#explode:{{Show|A|Veil of Discord|Spell Weakness|value3}}|%}}/100}}}}<!--
-->{{#vardefine:d5|{{Show|A|Dagon 5|Energy Burst|value2}}}}<!--
-->{{#vardefine:mage slayer|{{#expr:{{#explode:{{Show|A|Mage Slayer|Mage Slayer|value1}}|%}}/100}}}}
: {{H|Bloodseeker}} from the previous example has {{I|Dagon 5}} and is affected by {{A|Mage Slayer|Mage Slayer}}. How much actual spell damage {{A|Dagon|Energy Burst}} will be dealt to {{H|Marci}} if she is also affected by {{A|Veil of Discord|Spell Weakness}} (before [[magic resistance]] reductions)?
::* {{I|Dagon 5}} spell damage: {{#var:d5}}
::* Incoming Spell Damage Manipulation: {{A|Veil of Discord|Spell Weakness}}: {{#var:veil}}
::* Outgoing Spell Damage Manipulation: {{A|Bloodseeker|Bloodrage}}: {{#var:bloodrage}}, {{I|Kaya and Sange}}: {{#var:kns}}, {{A|Mage Slayer|Mage Slayer}}: -{{#var:mage slayer}}

: {{#tag:math|\begin{align}
Sp_{Mu} 
&= \underbrace{ (1 + ({{#var:bloodrage}} + {{#var:kns}} - {{#var:mage slayer}})) }_\text{Outgoing} \times \underbrace{ (1 + {{#var:veil}}) }_\text{Incoming} \\
&= \underbrace{ ({{#expr:1 + {{#var:bloodrage}} + {{#var:kns}} - {{#var:mage slayer}}}}) }_\text{Outgoing} \times \underbrace{ ({{#expr:1 + {{#var:veil}}}}) }_\text{Incoming} \\
&= {{#vardefineecho:spellexample2|{{#expr:(1+{{#var:bloodrage}}+{{#var:kns}}-{{#var:mage slayer}})*(1+{{#var:veil}})}}}}
\end{align}
}}

: {{#tag:math|
\text{Total Spell Damage} = {{#var:d5}} * {{#var:spellexample2}} = {{#vardefineecho:sumspdmg2|{{#expr:{{#var:d5}}*{{#var:spellexample2}}}}}}
}}

: {{H|Marci}} affected by {{A|Veil of Discord|Spell Weakness}} will take {{#var:sumspdmg2}} spell damage (before [[magic resistance]]) from {{H|Bloodseeker}} in this example.

====Example 3: Generic Damage Manipulation====<!--
-->{{#vardefine:dispersion|{{#expr:{{#explode:{{#explode:{{Show|A|Spectre|Dispersion|value3}}|/|3}}|%}}/100}}}}
: {{H|Bloodseeker}} from the previous example instead chooses to cast his {{I|Dagon 5}} on a {{H|Spectre}} with level 4 {{A|Spectre|Dispersion}}. Assuming all other modifiers are the same, how much spell damage will be dealt to {{H|Spectre}} (before magic resistance).
: Dispersion is generic damage manipulation, meaning it affects all damage dealt to {{H|Spectre}}. Despite this, it stacks additively with other incoming spell damage manipulation like {{A|Veil of Discord|Spell Weakness}} when calculating spell damage.
::* {{I|Dagon 5}} spell damage: {{#var:d5}}
::* Incoming Spell Damage Manipulation: {{A|Veil of Discord|Spell Weakness}}: {{#var:veil}}
::* Incoming Generic Damage Manipulation: {{A|Spectre|Dispersion}}: -{{#var:dispersion}}
::* Outgoing Spell Damage Manipulation: {{A|Bloodseeker|Bloodrage}}: {{#var:bloodrage}}, {{I|Kaya and Sange}}: {{#var:kns}}, {{A|Mage Slayer|Mage Slayer}}: -{{#var:mage slayer}}

: {{#tag:math|\begin{align}
Sp_{Mu} 
&= \underbrace{ (1 + ({{#var:bloodrage}} + {{#var:kns}} - {{#var:mage slayer}})) }_\text{Outgoing} \times \underbrace{ (1 + {{#var:veil}} - {{#var:dispersion}}) }_\text{Incoming} \\
&= \underbrace{ ({{#expr:1 + {{#var:bloodrage}} + {{#var:kns}} - {{#var:mage slayer}}}}) }_\text{Outgoing} \times \underbrace{ ({{#expr:1 + {{#var:veil}} - {{#var:dispersion}}}}) }_\text{Incoming} \\
&= {{#vardefineecho:spellexample3|{{#expr:(1+{{#var:bloodrage}}+{{#var:kns}}-{{#var:mage slayer}})*(1+{{#var:veil}} - {{#var:dispersion}})}}}}
\end{align}
}}

: {{#tag:math|
\text{Total Spell Damage} = {{#var:d5}} * {{#var:spellexample3}} = {{#vardefineecho:sumspdmg3|{{#expr:{{#var:d5}}*{{#var:spellexample3}}}}}}
}}

: {{H|Spectre}} affected by will take {{#var:sumspdmg3}} spell damage (before [[magic resistance]]) from {{H|Bloodseeker}} in this example.

===Incoming Spell Damage Amplification===
A unit that has incoming spell damage amplification debuff on them takes more spell damage, and multiple sources of incoming spell damage amplification stack additively. Incoming spell damage amplification affects every source of spell damage, except for damage flagged as [[HP Removal]].

